<pre class="r"><code>#Total number of steps taken per day

attach(TotNoStepsPerDay)

<ol start="2" style="list-style-type: decimal">
<li>Devise a strategy for filling in all of the missing values in the dataset. The strategy does not need to be sophisticated. For example, you could use the mean/median for that day, or the mean for that 5-minute interval, etc.</li>
</ol>
<p>The NAs values in the quantitative attributes will be replaced by the mean value and in the qualitative attributes will be replaced by the mode value.</p>
<ol start="3" style="list-style-type: decimal">
<li>The NAs values in the quantitative attributes will be replaced by the mean value and in the qualitative attributes will be replaced by the mode value.</li>
</ol>
<pre class="r"><code>#Missing insert function
missing.insert = function(x,na.string = NA){
  
if(missing(x))
  stop(&quot;You must specify a variable that stores data set!&quot;)

znak&lt;-as.character(na.string)
x&lt;-data.frame(x)
r&lt;-nrow(x)
c&lt;-ncol(x)

if(!is.na(znak)){
  for(i in 1:r){
    for(j in 1:c){
      if(x[i,j] == znak){
        x[i,j] &lt;- NA
      }
    }
  }
}

x2&lt;-na.omit(x)

for(k in 1:c){
  if(is.numeric(x2[,k])){
    meanX &lt;- mean(x2[,k])
    for(l in 1:r){
      if(is.na(x[l,k])){
        x[l,k] &lt;- meanX
      }
    }
  }else{
    modeX&lt;-names(sort(-table(x2[,k])))[1]
    for(l in 1:r){
      if(is.na(x[l,k])){
        x[l,k] &lt;- modeX
      }
    }
  }
}
return(x)
}

activityNAIns&lt;-missing.insert(activityNA)</code></pre>
